<div id="attachment_1070" style="width: 248px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><a href="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2015/05/RJD_04_01_0019_0006_001.jpg" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><img class="wp-image-1070 size-medium" src="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2015/05/RJD_04_01_0019_0006_001-238x300.jpg" alt="Richard J. Daley surrounded by five women wearing national costumes in honor of Captive Nations Week, 1960. Photo R. E. Murphy. RJD_04_01_0019_0006_001" width="238" height="300" srcset="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2015/05/RJD_04_01_0019_0006_001-238x300.jpg 238w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2015/05/RJD_04_01_0019_0006_001-812x1024.jpg 812w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2015/05/RJD_04_01_0019_0006_001-1080x1361.jpg 1080w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2015/05/RJD_04_01_0019_0006_001.jpg 1190w" sizes="(max-width: 238px) 100vw, 238px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Richard J. Daley surrounded by five women wearing national costumes in honor of Captive Nations Week, 1960. Photo R. E. Murphy. RJD_04_01_0019_0006_001</p></div></div>
							
